<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN280-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai - potuviyal; tuṟai - āṉantappaiyuḷ. māṟōkkattu nappacalaiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN280">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>eṉṉai mārpiṟ puṇṇum veyya</l>
<l>naṭunāḷ vantu tumpiyun tuvaikku</l>
<l>neṭunakar varaippiṉ viḷakku nillā</l>
<l>tuñcāk kaṇṇē tuyilum vēṭku</l>
<l>mañcuvaru kurāaṟ kuralun tūṟṟu</l>
<l>neṉṉī reṟintu viricci yōrkkuñ</l>
<l>cemmutu peṇṭiṉ collu nirampā</l>
<l>tuṭiya pāṇa pāṭuval viṟali</l>
<l>yeṉṉā kuvirko laḷiyir numakku</l>
<l>mivaṇuṟai vāḻkkaiyō varitē yāṉu</l>
<l>maṇṇuṟu maḻittalait teṇṇīr vārat</l>
<l>toṉṟutā muṭutta vampakait teriyaṟ</l>
<l>ciṟuveḷ ḷāmpa lalli yuṇṇuṅ</l>
<l>kaḻikala makaḷir pōla</l>
<l>vaḻiniṉain tirutta lataṉiṉu maritē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The wounds in my lord’s chest are severe,</l>
<l>coming at midday the bees hum,</l>
<l>no lamps stand within the boundaries of the large mansion,</l>
<l>[my] sleepless eyes, they long for sleep,</l>
<l>the fearful owl’s voice is spreading,</l>
<l>throwing paddy [and] water, [one?] listens to the disembodied voice,</l>
<l>and the words of upright old women do not come to a conclusion,</l>
<l>oh drummer, oh bard, oh dancing girl who masters singing,</l>
<l>what will [now] become of you? Pitiable you. For you too,</l>
<l>as for [making] a living while staying here, it will be difficult. For me too,</l>
<l>like [those] women whose ornaments have been discarded,</l>
<l>who eat little white lotus seeds,</l>
<l>with [their] pretty contrasting garlands that they put on of old,</l>
<l>while clear water runs down [their] bald head that were washed,</l>
<l>sitting [there] thinking of that way [to live] will be even more difficult that that.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
